{"word":"H6398 - פָּלַח - pâlach - paw-lakh' - Bring forth","slug":"H6398","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">פָּלַח</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>pâlach"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>paw-lakh'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Bring forth"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E4;&#x05BC;&#x05DC;&#x05D7; - pa&#x0302;lach</b> - <i>paw-lakh'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>slice</i>, that is, <i>break</i> open or <i>pierce: - </i>bring forth, cleave, cut, shred, strike through."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6400\">H6400</a>, <a href=\"#/H6401\">H6401</a>"}]}